\paragraph{Data Parameters (derived from attributes and relationships).}
Where needed, categorical attributes (e.g., \texttt{status}) are represented by numeric indicator parameters derived from the CSVs:
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=2em,itemsep=0.25em]
  \item $s^{\text{done}}_{u} \in \{0,1\}$ (\texttt{UserStory.status} == done), $\text{sp}_{u}\in\mathbb{Z}_{\ge0}$ (\texttt{UserStory.story\_points}).
  \item $e\!f\!f_{\tau} \in \mathbb{R}_{\ge0}$ (\texttt{Task.effort}), $is\_not\_done_f \in \{0,1\}$ (\texttt{Feature.status} $\neq$ done).
  \item $avail_{w} \in [0,1]$ (\texttt{Worker.availability}), $sev_{b} \in \mathbb{R}_{\ge0}$ (\texttt{Blocker.severity}).
  \item $cost_{f} \in \mathbb{R}_{\ge0}$ (proxy from \texttt{Feature.estimated\_effort} and unit cost).
  \item $rel_{sh,f} \in \mathbb{R}_{\ge0}$ (from \texttt{Stakeholder.relevance\_to\_feature}).
  \item $align_{f} \in \mathbb{R}_{\ge0}$ (alignment to \texttt{Roadmap.objectives}).
  \item $fbq_{sp} \in \mathbb{R}_{\ge0}$ (quality of \texttt{SprintReview.feedback\_documentation} for sprint $sp$).
\end{itemize}
Relationship-incidence parameters (from Relationships.csv):
\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=2em,itemsep=0.25em]
  \item $R^{US\text{-}TSK}_{u,\tau}\in\{0,1\}$ (R10: story $u$ consists of task $\tau$).
  \item $R^{PB\text{-}US}_{pb,u}\in\{0,1\}$ and $R^{PB\text{-}F}_{pb,f}\in\{0,1\}$ (R7, R11 via epic/story expansion).
  \item $R^{SBL\text{-}US}_{sbl,u}\in\{0,1\}$ (R11), $R^{SP\text{-}SBL}_{sp,sbl}\in\{0,1\}$ (R12), $R^{SP\text{-}SG}_{sp,sg}\in\{0,1\}$ (R13).
